<refentry xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:db="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" version="5.0-subset Scilab" xml:lang="en" xml:id="convex_hull">
  <info>
    <pubdate>$LastChangedDate$</pubdate>
  </info>
  <refnamediv>
    <refname>convex_hull</refname>
    <refpurpose> convex hull of a set of points in the plane</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <title>Calling Sequence</title>
    <synopsis>[nhull,ind] = convex_hull(xy)</synopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>
  <refsection>
    <title>Parameters</title>
    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>xy</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>2 x n real matrix</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>nhull</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>integer</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>ind</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>integer row vector</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </refsection>
  <refsection>
    <title>Description</title>
    <para><literal>convex_hull</literal> finds the convex hull of a given set of n points in
    the plane. <literal>xy</literal> is the 2 x n matrix of the (x,y) coordinates of
    the given points. <literal>convex_hull</literal> returns in <literal>nhull</literal> the number
    of the points of the boundary of the convex hull and in <literal>ind</literal> the
    row vector (of size <literal>nhull</literal>) giving the indices in <literal>xy</literal> of the
    points of the boundary. The order in <literal>ind</literal> corresponds to
    consecutive points on the boundary.</para>
  </refsection>
  <refsection>
    <title>Examples</title>
    <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[

ta=[27 27 3 12 11 12 27 26 26 25 25 24 23 23 21 22 21 20 19 18 18];
ta=[ta  16 15 15 14 12 9 10 6 9 17 8 17 10 20 11 23 23 12 18 28]; 
he=[ 1  2 2  4  5 11 13  1 25 22 24 22 22 19 13 13 14 16 16  9 16];
he=[he  10 10 11 12  2 6  5 5 7  8 7  9  6 11  4 18 13  3 28 17];
g=make_graph('foo',0,28,ta,he);
xx=[46 120 207 286 366 453 543 544 473 387 300 206 136 250 346 408];
g.nodes.graphics.x=[xx 527 443 306 326 196 139 264  55  58  46 118 513];
yy=[36  34  37  40  38  40  35 102 102  98  93  96 167 172 101 179];
g.nodes.graphics.y=[yy 198 252 183 148 172 256 259 258 167 109 104 253];
show_graph(g);
xy=[g.nodes.graphics.x;g.nodes.graphics.y];
[nhull,ind] = convex_hull(xy)
hilite_nodes(ind);
 
  ]]></programlisting>
  </refsection>
</refentry>
